{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a8630c73-91eb-4622-a69d-1945f87af4fd","content":"For ASP.NET Core, use the **`webapi`** template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Example with auth:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain mydomain.onmicrosoft.com\n```\n\n**Other relevant templates:**\n- `webapi-aot` — minimal API with native AOT\n- `webapiauthentication-k8s` — Kubernetes-ready with auth\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` to see all options for your installed SDK version. Would you like help scaffolding a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3630b403-f306-4f7f-a639-021d0e7bbf94","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET development question. Let me check if there's relevant content in the repository that might help answer this, particularly in the plugins directory.\n\nActually, looking at the context, this is a general question about creating a web API project with authentication. This is likely about .NET/ASP.NET Core templates. I can answer this from general knowledge without needing to search the repository, unless there are relevant plugins or docs here.\n\nLet me just answer from knowledge since this is a general development question.","outputTokens":372,"requestId":"7409:28231D:1C2F063:1F2DE03:69FA8FCD"},"id":"d2b62e29-d782-4dbe-bb65-99a18834941d","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:48:23.989Z","parentId":"d8d4f973-9a7d-421f-82e5-37d419cbfade"}
